cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.GR 

The paper deals with image classification using deep learning techniques, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and spatial pyramid pooling (SPP-net) also indicates that it may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves feature extraction and kernel learning, which are common topics in information retrieval (cs.IR) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
